---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Benchmark Progress"
  description="Track your progress on official KovaaK's benchmarks."
  prevPage={{ slug: "sessions", title: "Sessions" }}
  nextPage={{ slug: "mouse-tracking", title: "Mouse Movement" }}
>
  <h2>Official Benchmarks</h2>
  <p>
    RefleK's includes all major KovaaK's benchmarks so you can track your
    progress toward rank goals. Your progress updates automatically as you play
    benchmark scenarios.
  </p>

  <div class="image-container">
    <img
      src="/assets/images/benchmarks_explore.webp"
      alt="Benchmark tracking"
      loading="lazy"
    />
  </div>

  <h2>How It Works</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Browse available benchmarks in the Benchmarks page</li>
    <li>Select a benchmark and difficulty level</li>
    <li>Play benchmark scenarios in KovaaK's</li>
    <li>Your scores are tracked automatically</li>
    <li>Progress bars show your current rank tier</li>
    <li>See exactly what scores you need for the next rank</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Launch Playlists</h2>
  <p>Start practicing directly from RefleK's:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Click the play button on any benchmark</li>
    <li>The benchmark playlist launches in KovaaK's</li>
    <li>Your runs are tracked automatically as you play</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Steam Integration</h2>
  <p>
    RefleK's detects your Steam username automatically and uses it to fetch your
    benchmark progress from the KovaaK's servers.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Your Steam username or ID is detected automatically from your local Steam
      installation
    </li>
    <li>
      Rankings are fetched from KovaaK's servers when you open the Benchmarks
      page
    </li>
    <li>No Steam profile visibility settings required</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Favorites & Visibility</h2>
  <p>Focus on what matters with favorites and visibility controls:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Favorites:</strong> Star benchmarks for quick access at the top of the
      list
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Hide ranks:</strong> Hide rank tiers you've already achieved or don't
      care about
    </li>
    <li><strong>Auto-hide:</strong> Automatically hide completed ranks</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Benchmark Analysis</h2>
  <p>For each benchmark, RefleK's provides:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Overview:</strong> Your current rank, progress, and scores for each
      scenario
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Analysis:</strong> Performance trends and score history charts
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Scenario history:</strong> Click any scenario to see your run history
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Benchmark Recommendations</h2>
  <p>
    On the Explore page, enable recommendations to see which benchmarks you
    should focus on. Click the sparkle button in the toolbar to toggle
    recommendations on or off.
  </p>
  <p>
    RefleK's prioritizes benchmarks based on your progression state - it favors
    benchmarks you've started but not finished, suggests next steps in your
    ladder, and adjusts recommendations for beginners who are just getting
    started.
  </p>

  <div class="image-container">
    <img
      src="/assets/images/benchmark_explore_recom.webp"
      alt="Benchmark recommendations in Explore view"
      loading="lazy"
    />
  </div>

  <h2>Scenario Recommendations</h2>
  <p>
    Inside a benchmark, RefleK's analyzes your progress and recommends which
    scenarios to play next:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Top Picks:</strong> Special recommendations based on high potential,
      category diversity, and recent focus areas
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Priority scenarios:</strong> Scenarios where you're closest to ranking
      up
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Weak points:</strong> Scenarios holding back your overall rank
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Quick wins:</strong> Where a small improvement would have the biggest
      impact
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Look for the recommendation icons next to scenarios - they show you exactly
    where to focus your practice for the fastest rank progression.
  </p>

  <h2>Share Your Progress</h2>
  <p>Share your benchmark progress with one click:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Open a benchmark</li>
    <li>Click the camera/share button</li>
    <li>A polished image of your progress is copied to clipboard</li>
    <li>Paste it in Discord, Twitter, or anywhere else</li>
  </ol>

  <div class="image-container">
    <img
      src="/assets/images/share.webp"
      alt="Share your benchmark progress"
      loading="lazy"
    />
  </div>

  <div class="note">
    <strong>Tip:</strong> The share image includes your scores, ranks, and progress
    bars - perfect for showing off your improvement!
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
